comments.text:
As a psychologist practicing in the United States with roots in India and over 25 years of experience, I am deeply disturbed by this situation. Its evident that the individual was battling trauma and depression, yet no measures were taken to prioritize their mental health. The judiciarys first responsibility should have been to ensure their well-being, offering treatment and family support.

Instead, the individual is left to perceive the system as complicit in their sufferinga failure not only of the judicial process but also of basic human rights. This incident underscores the urgent need for reforms to integrate mental health evaluations into legal proceedings. Protecting the right to live a healthy life should never be secondary to procedural formalities.

It is high time we wake up and demand a system that values human dignity above all
